34#include <subdev/i2c.h>

36static bool
37mxm_shadow_rom_fetch(struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus, u8 addr,
38 u8 offset, u8 size, u8 *data)
39{
40 struct i2c_msg msgs[] = {
41 { .addr = addr, .flags = 0, .len = 1, .buf = &offset },
42 { .addr = addr, .flags = I2C_M_RD, .len = size, .buf = data, },
43 };
44
45 return i2c_transfer(&bus->i2c, msgs, 2) == 2;
46}
47
48static bool
49mxm_shadow_rom(struct nvkm_mxm *mxm, u8 version)
50{
51 struct nvkm_device *device = mxm->subdev.device;
52 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
53 struct nvkm_i2c *i2c = device->i2c;
54 struct nvkm_i2c_bus *bus = NULL;
55 u8 i2cidx, mxms[6], addr, size;
56
57 i2cidx = mxm_ddc_map(bios, 1 /* LVDS_DDC */) & 0x0f;
58 if (i2cidx < 0x0f)
59 bus = nvkm_i2c_bus_find(i2c, i2cidx);
60 if (!bus)
61 return false;
62
63 addr = 0x54;
64 if (!mxm_shadow_rom_fetch(bus, addr, 0, 6, mxms)) {
65 addr = 0x56;
66 if (!mxm_shadow_rom_fetch(bus, addr, 0, 6, mxms))
67 return false;
68 }
69
70 mxm->mxms = mxms;
71 size = mxms_headerlen(mxm) + mxms_structlen(mxm);
72 mxm->mxms = kmalloc(size, GFP_KERNEL);
73
74 if (mxm->mxms &&
75 mxm_shadow_rom_fetch(bus, addr, 0, size, mxm->mxms))
76 return true;
77
78 kfree(mxm->mxms);
79 mxm->mxms = NULL;
80 return false;
81}
82
83#if defined(CONFIG_ACPI)
84static bool
85mxm_shadow_dsm(struct nvkm_mxm *mxm, u8 version)
86{
87 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &mxm->subdev;
88 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
89 static char muid[] = {
90 0x00, 0xA4, 0x04, 0x40, 0x7D, 0x91, 0xF2, 0x4C,
91 0xB8, 0x9C, 0x79, 0xB6, 0x2F, 0xD5, 0x56, 0x65
92 };
93 u32 mxms_args[] = { 0x00000000 };
94 union acpi_object argv4 = {
95 .buffer.type = ACPI_TYPE_BUFFER,
96 .buffer.length = sizeof(mxms_args),
97 .buffer.pointer = (char *)mxms_args,
98 };
99 union acpi_object *obj;
100 acpi_handle handle;
101 int rev;
102
103 handle = ACPI_HANDLE(device->dev);
104 if (!handle)
105 return false;
106
107 /*
108 * spec says this can be zero to mean "highest revision", but
109 * of course there's at least one bios out there which fails
110 * unless you pass in exactly the version it supports..
111 */
112 rev = (version & 0xf0) << 4 | (version & 0x0f);
113 obj = acpi_evaluate_dsm(handle, muid, rev, 0x00000010, &argv4);
114 if (!obj) {
115 nvkm_debug(subdev, "DSM MXMS failed\n");
116 return false;
117 }
118
119 if (obj->type == ACPI_TYPE_BUFFER) {
120 mxm->mxms = kmemdup(obj->buffer.pointer,
121 obj->buffer.length, GFP_KERNEL);
122 } else if (obj->type == ACPI_TYPE_INTEGER) {
123 nvkm_debug(subdev, "DSM MXMS returned 0x%"PRIx64"\n",
124 obj->integer.value);
125 }
126
127 ACPI_FREE(obj);
128 return mxm->mxms != NULL;
129}
130#endif
131
132#if defined(CONFIG_ACPI_WMI) || defined(CONFIG_ACPI_WMI_MODULE)
133
134#define WMI_WMMX_GUID "F6CB5C3C-9CAE-4EBD-B577-931EA32A2CC0"
135
136static u8
137wmi_wmmx_mxmi(struct nvkm_mxm *mxm, u8 version)
138{
139 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &mxm->subdev;
140 u32 mxmi_args[] = { 0x494D584D /* MXMI */, version, 0 };
141 struct acpi_buffer args = { sizeof(mxmi_args), mxmi_args };
142 struct acpi_buffer retn = { ACPI_ALLOCATE_BUFFER, NULL };
143 union acpi_object *obj;
144 acpi_status status;
145
146 status = wmi_evaluate_method(WMI_WMMX_GUID, 0, 0, &args, &retn);
147 if (ACPI_FAILURE(status)) {
148 nvkm_debug(subdev, "WMMX MXMI returned %d\n", status);
149 return 0x00;
150 }
151
152 obj = retn.pointer;
153 if (obj->type == ACPI_TYPE_INTEGER) {
154 version = obj->integer.value;
155 nvkm_debug(subdev, "WMMX MXMI version %d.%d\n",
156 (version >> 4), version & 0x0f);
157 } else {
158 version = 0;
159 nvkm_debug(subdev, "WMMX MXMI returned non-integer\n");
160 }
161
162 kfree(obj);
163 return version;
164}
165
166static bool
167mxm_shadow_wmi(struct nvkm_mxm *mxm, u8 version)
168{
169 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &mxm->subdev;
170 u32 mxms_args[] = { 0x534D584D /* MXMS */, version, 0 };
171 struct acpi_buffer args = { sizeof(mxms_args), mxms_args };
172 struct acpi_buffer retn = { ACPI_ALLOCATE_BUFFER, NULL };
173 union acpi_object *obj;
174 acpi_status status;
175
176 if (!wmi_has_guid(WMI_WMMX_GUID)) {
177 nvkm_debug(subdev, "WMMX GUID not found\n");
178 return false;
179 }
180
181 mxms_args[1] = wmi_wmmx_mxmi(mxm, 0x00);
182 if (!mxms_args[1])
183 mxms_args[1] = wmi_wmmx_mxmi(mxm, version);
184 if (!mxms_args[1])
185 return false;
186
187 status = wmi_evaluate_method(WMI_WMMX_GUID, 0, 0, &args, &retn);
188 if (ACPI_FAILURE(status)) {
189 nvkm_debug(subdev, "WMMX MXMS returned %d\n", status);
190 return false;
191 }
192
193 obj = retn.pointer;
194 if (obj->type == ACPI_TYPE_BUFFER) {
195 mxm->mxms = kmemdup(obj->buffer.pointer,
196 obj->buffer.length, GFP_KERNEL);
197 }
198
199 kfree(obj);
200 return mxm->mxms != NULL;
201}
202#endif
203
204static struct mxm_shadow_h {
205 const char *name;
206 bool (*exec)(struct nvkm_mxm *, u8 version);
207} _mxm_shadow[] = {
208 { "ROM", mxm_shadow_rom },
209#if defined(CONFIG_ACPI)
210 { "DSM", mxm_shadow_dsm },
211#endif
212#if defined(CONFIG_ACPI_WMI) || defined(CONFIG_ACPI_WMI_MODULE)
213 { "WMI", mxm_shadow_wmi },
214#endif
215 {}
216};
217
218static int
219mxm_shadow(struct nvkm_mxm *mxm, u8 version)
220{
221 struct mxm_shadow_h *shadow = _mxm_shadow;
222 do {
223 nvkm_debug(&mxm->subdev, "checking %s\n", shadow->name);
224 if (shadow->exec(mxm, version)) {
225 if (mxms_valid(mxm))
226 return 0;
227 kfree(mxm->mxms);
228 mxm->mxms = NULL;
229 }
230 } while ((++shadow)->name);
231 return -ENOENT;
232}
233
234static const struct nvkm_subdev_func
235nvkm_mxm = {
236};
237
238int
239nvkm_mxm_new_(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_mxm **pmxm)
240{
241 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
242 struct nvkm_mxm *mxm;
243 u8 ver, len;
244 u16 data;
245
246 if (!(mxm = *pmxm = kzalloc(sizeof(*mxm), GFP_KERNEL)))
247 return -ENOMEM;
248
249 nvkm_subdev_ctor(&nvkm_mxm, device, index, 0, &mxm->subdev);
250
251 data = mxm_table(bios, &ver, &len);
252 if (!data || !(ver = nvbios_rd08(bios, data))) {
253 nvkm_debug(&mxm->subdev, "no VBIOS data, nothing to do\n");
254 return 0;
255 }
256
257 nvkm_info(&mxm->subdev, "BIOS version %d.%d\n", ver >> 4, ver & 0x0f);
258
259 if (mxm_shadow(mxm, ver)) {
260 nvkm_warn(&mxm->subdev, "failed to locate valid SIS\n");
261#if 0
262 /* we should, perhaps, fall back to some kind of limited
263 * mode here if the x86 vbios hasn't already done the
264 * work for us (so we prevent loading with completely
265 * whacked vbios tables).
266 */
267 return -EINVAL;
268#else
269 return 0;
270#endif
271 }
272
273 nvkm_debug(&mxm->subdev, "MXMS Version %d.%d\n",
274 mxms_version(mxm) >> 8, mxms_version(mxm) & 0xff);
275 mxms_foreach(mxm, 0, NULL, NULL);
276
277 if (nvkm_boolopt(device->cfgopt, "NvMXMDCB", true))
278 mxm->action |= MXM_SANITISE_DCB;
279 return 0;
280}
